entHandler for database connections, and RequestThreadLoopHandler to manage the loop processing.\n\nNow checking the duplicate launch error flow - it follows a similar initial path through Main and ThreadContextHandler_main, but then DuplicateProcessCheckHandler intercepts to set the exit code during shutdown, GlobalErrorHandler logs the failure, and the response flows back through StatusCodeConvertHandler before Main exits abnormally.\n\nFor the normal reply flow, RequestPathJavaPackageMapping routes the incoming request to AsyncMessageReceiveAction for dispatching.\n\nContinuing with the message receive flow - ThreadLoopHandler serves as the entry point, followed by ThreadContextHandler_request and TransactionManagementHandler to set up the context, then DataReadHandler_messaging waits for the actual message data before AsyncMessageReceiveAction processes it and returns control back through the transaction and thread loop handlers.\n\nWhen a read timeout occurs, DataReadHandler_messaging returns NoMoreRecord after the timeout expires, which signals RequestThreadLoopHandler to move to the next phase, and ProcessStopHandler begins the shutdown sequence.\n\nAfter checking for lag, the flow cycles back to DataReadHandler_messaging to wait for the next message.\n\nFor reception errors, when AsyncMessageReceiveAction encounters a format error in the message data, it throws a runtime exception that gets caught by TransactionManagementHandler in error state, then RequestThreadLoopHandler logs the failure and transitions to the next phase.\n\nFor authorization errors, PermissionCheckHandler detects insufficient permissions and returns a 403 Forbidden status, which TransactionManagementHandler catches in error state before RequestThreadLoopHandler outputs the exception log and moves forward.\n\nFor the service unavailability check, ServiceAvailabilityCheckHandler validates whether the service is currently operational. リトライハンドラーがMQとDB接続を再確立してから、最初のステップに戻るフローになっている。正常停止の場合は、リ