anese text about configuration changes, so it should be included in s1's hints. I'm also noticing that some explanatory content from the intro section about the framework's business action handlers doesn't appear to be captured in the knowledge file's s1 section.\n\nThe information is actually present in s2 though, just restructured differently. I'm also catching some minor terminology variations like 既定 versus 規定 for \"predetermined number of times,\" which are functionally equivalent. The RST horizontal rule separators in the source are just formatting elements, so those don't need to be flagged. Let me continue checking for any other discrepancies I might have overlooked. The only substantive issue I found is that the s1 hints are missing `TransactionManagementHandler`, which is explicitly mentioned as a class name in the s1 content itself. Otherwise, the knowledge file is quite thorough and accurate.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24213,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":24213,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f541793-8669-4d9d-af8b-4fa5a63476f2","uuid":"3fed8635-1582-4662-b954-996c8458cd66"}
